HEADWORD: Stavesacre
<hw>Staves"a`cre</hw> <pr>(st⟦amac⟧vz"⟦amac⟧`k⟦etil⟧r)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Corrupted from NL. <ets>staphis agria</ets>, Gr.
<grk>stafi`s</grk> dried grape + <grk>'a`grios</grk> wild.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A kind of larkspur (<spn>Delphinium
Staphysagria</spn>), and its seeds, which are violently purgative and
emetic. They are used as a parasiticide, and in the East for poisoning
fish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stavewood</ent>⟦br⟧
